social_posts.post_text: Yesterday Ukraine celebrated Vyshyvanka Day. Vyshyvanka is part of Ukrainian traditional clothing featuring embroidery specific to Ukraine's culture with variations unique to the country's regions. Even though it is a day late, here’s a picture of us wearing vyshyvankas after getting haircut from the best @jhzara
Stepping back in time at Musee d’Orsay. One of my favorite places in Paris.
Holy crêpe, it's the Eiffel Tower!

location.city_name: Trinity College Old Library & The Book of Kells Exhibition

social_posts.post_text: “I have always imagined that Paradise will be a kind of library.” - Jorge Luis Borges. This quote is posted at the entrance of the Trinity College Long Hall Library and I can’t agree more! My favorite place.

Happy Pride!! 🏳️‍🌈 Pride is about love, acceptance, and self-worth. No one should live in fear because of who they are or who they love. Love is a beautiful force that should never be concealed or judged. I am so incredibly grateful for the love I have found, as it has brought so much joy and fulfillment to my life. Love you, my darling!

Pride is also an act of resistance. As we celebrate Pride, we should resist the renewed assault on LGBTQI+ rights and humanity. In the words of Marsha P. Johnson “No Pride for some of us without liberation for all of us.”

Finally back in my regalia after a 3 year COVID hiatus! Seeing fresh graduates stepping into the professional world is incredibly inspiring. Grateful and humbled to receive the faculty award for research excellence during the graduation. 🎓💪
Comedy night at the Britely and we ended up seeing a surprise headliner - Eliza Shlesinger! Long weekend is off to a great start.
This 4th of July weekend is all about palm trees and 100 degrees #palmsprings
Happy 4th of July from #palmsprings
Vegas for our friends’ wedding! I wonder if “what happens in Vegas, stays in Vegas” also applies to a few extra pounds I may get here 🍔🌮
Having a tea-rrific time with parents at the @theshelbournedublin trying our best to recreate a scene from Bridgerton

“Love is a friendship set to music.” A few highlights from the best day of my life, marrying my soulmate @derekmckellar Stay tuned for more glimpses of our special day. Here’s our first dance as husbands. Much gratitude to @_vecherskiy_kos for the choreography and patience. 💖🕺 #FirstDance #HappilyEverAfter #wedding #weddingday #weddingdance #love #grooms #instawedding #loveislove #lovewins #gaywedding #ireland #dublin

More wedding highlights: the ceremony led by @hitched_by_connie, beautifully featured several rituals like handfasting and our love story turned into a bespoke poem. There wasn’t a dry eye in the audience. The video’s soundtrack was performed live along with a few others by the awesome Irish band @bentleyboysband
Found these videos by @infusionweddings and @irishweddingblog showing our 🏰 wedding venue and behind the scenes magic of the day

While watching Zelenskyy's Independence Day speech today, I admired his embroidered shirt by Ukrainian designer @gasanova_elvira . Elvira often dresses the Ukrainian First Lady and she also dressed me for my wedding! My traditional wedding outfit was one of the most cherished gifts, designed by my friend - amazing fashion stylist @maxgor . Max sent his concept to Elvira and she created such a unique handmade piece. I'm incredibly grateful for this one-of-a-kind outfit that beautifully merges tradition and modernity. My gratitude is only matched by my thoughts and prayers for every Ukrainian fighting for freedom.

Home sweet home, Los Angeles! 🏡🌴 After a sweet escape to Paris 🇫🇷 for our mini-honeymoon, it's back to reality. First order of business: a fresh haircut from the incredible @jhzara , the hair wizard who worked magic on us for the big day! 💇‍♂️

When work takes you from the nation’s capital to the iconic streets of🗽🏙️ NYC. After wrapping up the conference in DC this weekend, I hopped on a train to be in Manhattan for a few meetings. Feel lucky to explore the city and visit a few of my favorite places.

A throwback to our mini-honeymoon in Paris, captured beautifully by a talented Ukrainian artist @tomusiak.irina we met on our trip. In the midst of Parisian heatwave, a chance rain washed away crowds when we took these pictures. No tourists, just us and the magic of Paris in the rain. 👨‍❤️‍👨🌧️
Looking back at my happy moments in Paris like they are a box of delightful macarons #sweetmemories

🎉 Today's my birthday, and I'm incredibly grateful for all the love and messages I've received! 🙏 But the most amazing gift you can give me is your support for a cause close to my heart. 🇺🇦 I’m raising funds for my friends on the Ukrainian frontlines (now Kherson) to buy batteries for their drones and an additional one for reconnaissance. No donation is too small. If you'd like to make my birthday extra special, please consider treating me to a coffee using the link below 🎁 Let's stand together for Ukraine! 💙

https://www.buymeacoffee.com/AlexUA

World’s steepest zipline! I’ve done it last year and thought I’d try it again. Such a thrill to get launched from 2800ft altitude! The gorgeous scenery is definitely a bonus. In the video is a kid who was flying before me…

We went sailing abroad an America Cup race boat. 🌊⛵️It is such an experience to be a part of a sailboat race - chasing the wind, performing maneuvers, and beating the competition. 🏁🏆 You can see my happy face before the race and then our speeding boat during the race.
Sand between your toes and planes overhead - thats the famous Maho Beach. Feeling the breeze as jumbo jets soar just feet above - a beach day like no other!
Warm wishes for 2024! May your joy be deep as the ocean and your worries light as it’s foam!
Making memories with you is my favorite thing to do.

Enjoining our final beach moments in the paradise🌴 During this trip, spotted some très intéressant (and très French) beach scenes:
- Some beaches here have reusable Cola cans that serve as ashtrays
- A unique blend of beachgoers - fashionistas in designer swimwear beside the au naturel folks.
- Stumbled upon a beach nook proudly flying the LGBTQ flag and dishing out French gourmet meals (picture boeuf bourguignon) instead of soggy sandwiches one might expect from a similar place in the US.
- Occasional yachts just off the coast, their crew setting up a seaside picnic for the yacht people. 
- And a dash of adorable – swimming with sea turtles 🐢
